The paper deals with the value distribution of exponential sums and their applications in coding theory and sequence design. This falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of trace mappings and the study of weight distribution of cyclic codes suggest a connection to algebraic coding theory and algebraic geometry (cs.DS). The determination of correlation distribution among a family of m-sequences suggests a connection to signal processing and communication theory (cs.SI). Finally, the study of binary cyclic codes and their weight distribution suggests a connection to network information theory (cs.NI).
